Note, the talk is announced with the title &amp;lsquo;&amp;lsquo;Music Information &amp;amp; Music Data&amp;rsquo;&amp;rsquo;.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Workshop at AIxMusic Festival in scope of the 2019 Ars Electronica Festival</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/post/_posts_wordpress/2019-08-27-workshop-at-aixmusic/</link><pubDate>Tue, 27 Aug 2019 21:41:34 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/post/_posts_wordpress/2019-08-27-workshop-at-aixmusic/</guid><description>&lt;p>I happily announce that I will hold a workshop with the title &lt;a href="https://ars.electronica.art/outofthebox/en/aixmusic-tools/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Recommenders and Intelligent Tools in Music Creation: Why, Why Not, and How?&lt;/a> at &lt;a href="https://ars.electronica.art/outofthebox/en/aixmusic/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">AIxMusic Festival&lt;/a> in scope of the &lt;a href="https://ars.electronica.art/outofthebox/en/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">2019 Ars Electronica Festival&lt;/a> – together with my co-speakers &lt;a href="https://www.ifs.tuwien.ac.at/~knees/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Peter Knees&lt;/a>, &lt;a href="https://www.ifs.tuwien.ac.at/~vogl/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Richard Vogl&lt;/a>, and &lt;a href="https://asdfg.me" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Hansi Raber&lt;/a>.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>